</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/10dbe62b924dc2e27e6fc6994d1303a6e40cdedb" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:14.76ex; height:5.676ex;" alt="{\frac {1}{f}}={\frac {1}{f_{1}}}+{\frac {1}{f_{2}}}."/></span><span about="#mwt288">
</span></dd></dl>

<p id="mwAdA">Since 1/<i id="mwAdE">f</i> is the power of a lens, it can be seen that the powers of thin lenses in contact are additive.</p>

<p id="mwAdI">If two thin lenses are separated in air by some distance <i id="mwAdM">d</i>, the focal length for the combined system is given by</p>

<dl id="mwAdQ"><dd id="mwAdU"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt290" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"\\frac{1}{f} = \\frac{1}{f_1} + \\frac{1}{f_2}-\\frac{d}{f_1 f_2}."}}' id="mwAdY"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle {\frac {1}{f}}={\frac {1}{f_{1}}}+{\frac {1}{f_{2}}}-{\frac {d}{f_{1}f_{2}}}.}">
