<p id="mwAdc">The distance from the front focal point of the combined lenses to the first lens is called the <i id="mwAdg">front focal length</i> (FFL):</p>

<dl id="mwAdk"><dd id="mwAdo"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt292" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"{\\mbox{FFL}} = \\frac{f_{1}(f_{2} - d)}{(f_1 + f_2) - d} ."}}' id="mwAds"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle {\mbox{FFL}}={\frac {f_{1}(f_{2}-d)}{(f_{1}+f_{2})-d}}.}">
